UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Miguel DOMINGO, Defendant-Appellant. No. 07-10437

Non-Argument Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. Feb. 26, 2008. Paul Rhinehart Jones, Amy Levin Weil, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Atlanta, GA, for Plaintiff-Appellee. *886Miguel Domingo, McRae, GA, for Defendant-Appellant. Before ANDERSON, WILSON and PRYOR, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM:

Michael R. Duponte, retained counsel for Miguel Domingo in this direct criminal appeal, has moved to withdraw from further representation of the appellant and filed a brief pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Our independent review of the entire record reveals that counsel’s assessment of the relative merit of the appeal is correct. As independent examination of the entire record reveals no arguable issues of merit, counsel’s motion to withdraw is GRANTED, and Domingo’s convictions and sentences are AFFIRMED.
